summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming its resolutions on Cyprus, particularly resolution 1251 (1999),
Welcoming the Secretary-General's report on UNFICYP and review of the operation,
Reiterating its call to address the humanitarian issue of missing persons,
Welcoming the resumption of the Committee on Missing Persons,
Noting the Government of Cyprus' agreement to keep UNFICYP beyond 15 December 2004,
Taking note of the benign security situation on the island,
Welcoming the Secretary-General's intention to review UNFICYP's mandate,
Echoing gratitude to contributors to UNFICYP's funding and requesting further contributions,
Welcoming efforts to sensitize peacekeeping personnel on HIV/AIDS prevention,

1. Reaffirms its relevant resolutions on Cyprus, particularly resolution 1251 (1999);
2. Endorses the Secretary-General's recommendations for UNFICYP's concept of operations and force level;
3. Extends UNFICYP's mandate until 15 June 2005;
4. Urges the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces to rescind restrictions on UNFICYP and restore the military status quo in Strovilia;
5. Requests a report on implementation of this resolution;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
